Description: Lip sherd of East Greek pottery bowl; interior: glazed dark brown with red stripe painted on lower part of fragment; exterior: top of lip glazed, reserved lip zone; glazed below; inscription cut on exterior in reserved zone.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 306)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 669, no. 267)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.372)
